name":"grrm","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"grrm","ctime_ts":1415823322,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/389280.html?thread=19735456#t19735456","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/389280.html?thread=19735456#t19735456","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/389280.html?thread=19735456#t19735456","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"guessingo","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://guessingo.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19735456,"talkid":77091,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/389280.html?thread=19735456#t19735456","upictitle":"guessingo: pic#0","article":"I have never been to a con. This is one of the few near my house (I live near Dulles Airport) and they just extended the train out here. I was thinking about hopping on a train and checking it out. It looks like more of a trade convention for professional writers/editors, etc... but they seemed to have some stuff for fans.\n\nI forgot all about it. Damn. This makes me feel old and senile. \n\nCongrats George on the win. I hope they gave out two trophies so you don't have to share. ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"November 12 2014, 21:14:56 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"damn i was going to go to world fantasy...","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://guessingo.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"guessingo","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"guessingo","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://guessingo.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"guessingo","ctime_ts":1415826896,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/46347849/2210042","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/389280.html?thread=19735968#t19735968","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/389280.html?thread=19735968#t19735968","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/389280.html?thread=19735968#t19735968","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"dragondances","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://dragondances.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19735968,"talkid":77093,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/389280.html?thread=19735968#t19735968","upictitle":"dragondances: Confetti by orangepenguino","article":"Congratulations on your win!<br /><br />Out of curiosity (as a long-time reader and fan of yours), I was wondering if you have an opinion about the statuette controversy? Obviously you have some history with the Award, having won in previous years and being proud of displaying it, and I imagine you're a fan of HPL himself. I just didn't know if it's something you're trying to stay out of until the dust settles (which would totally make sense) or if you're either for or against changing the statuette?<br />","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"November 12 2014, 21:55:43 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://dragondances.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"dragondances","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"dragondances","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://dragondances.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"dragondances","ctime_ts":1415829343,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/91237832/7059164","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/389280.html?thread=19736224#t19736224","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/389280.html?thread=19736224#t19736224","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/389280.html?thread=19736224#t19736224","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"grrm","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19736224,"talkid":77094,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/389280.html?thread=19736224#t19736224","above":19735968,"upictitle":"George R.R. Martin: Spain","article":"I like the statuette.  I count myself a Lovecraft fan, and a fan of Gahan Wilson, the sculptor, as well.  Yes, the bust is ugly, but strikingly so, and that's part of its charm.  It was always meant to be a caricature, and to be it evokes the Deep Ones and Easter Island as much as HPL's own facial features.<br /><br />For all his flaws, Lovecraft's work seems to have stood the test of time, and influenced many later writers, myself included.  And his best stories are very good indeed.  He died eleven years before I was born, so of course I never knew him... but those who did tell us that he was a kind and generous soul, a gentle man as well as a gentleman.  That counts for a lot with me.  There are some ugly passages in some of his work, that cannot be denied, but from what I've read, HPL was never less than courteous towards those he encountered in real life.  ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"November 12 2014, 22:50:03 UTC","parent":19735968,"massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"grrm","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"grrm","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"grrm","ctime_ts":1415832603,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/115429295/2210042","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/389280.html?thread=19736736#t19736736","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/389280.html?thread=19736736#t19736736","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/389280.html?thread=19736736#t19736736","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"dragondances","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://dragondances.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19736736,"talkid":77096,"etime_ts":"1415840121","thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/389280.html?thread=19736736#t19736736","above":19736224,"upictitle":"dragondances: out of context by ani defranco/enriana","article":"Thank you for taking the time to answer! A lot of people have really strong emotions about it one way or the other, and for good reasons in both cases. I love HPL as well! It's definitely true that his work is formative despite his less-than-savory opinions on certain topics. It's a good point to look at his actions as well as his written opinions, though. <br /><br />Again, I really do appreciate your courtesy in responding. :)","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"November 13 2014, 00:50:28 UTC","parent":19736224,"massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://dragondances.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alia